##How does Wuhan Start The economic "recovery war" with finance occupying half of Hubei Province

Wuhan's top priority

It is to seek a balance between scientific anti-epidemic and orderly resumption of work

Workers work on the construction site of the Lei Shen Shan Hospital in Wuhan, China, Feb. 3,2010. During the outbreak, new Wuhan Fire Mountain, Thor Mountain Hospital, converted into a Shelter Hospital 33, provide shelter hospital beds 35,673. Photograph: Chen Liang for Changjiang daily

Under the new crown epidemic situation strict prevention and control request, the whole country enters the resumption of production stage.

On March 13, at a press conference of the Joint Defense and Joint Control Mechanism of the State Council, Ministry of Industry and Information Technology of the People's Republic of China, a Vice Minister of the State Council, revealed that the average operating rate of industrial enterprises above the scale except Hubei is over 95 percent, the average rate of returning to work is about 80% , and the operating rate of small and medium-sized enterprises has reached about 60% .

Even in Hubei Province, where the outbreak is most severe, cities with low levels of the epidemic are beginning to deploy back to work in an orderly manner, and the economy is expected to restart.

But for Wuhan, which was the first to shut down, a full resumption of work is not promising. At present, the task of epidemic prevention and control is still arduous, the time of large-scale resumption of work is still uncertain, and its economic losses are gradually expanding, which may have medium-and long-term effects on the economic operation of Wuhan.

"The first quarter will definitely have a big impact, " an official at the Wuhan Municipal Development and Reform Commission, who did not want to be named, told China News weekly recently. Many of the figures are now basically zero. In southern cities like Wuhan, as in previous years, the first quarter is a promising start. But the economic indicators for the first quarter of this year have been largely missed by the outbreak, and the Wuhan government will face a huge test of how the economy can remedy the situation and help businesses survive.

Economic Pain

In early March, at a press conference of the Joint Defense and Control Mechanism of the State Council, Xu Hongcai, deputy minister of Finance, revealed to the outside world that general public budget revenue in Hubei Province had maintained growth in January, and that the situation had changed considerably in February, only sporadic revenue into the treasury, into March, the Treasury will still maintain sporadic revenue into the treasury.

It is conceivable that Wuhan, which accounts for half of Hubei's financial revenue, could expect its financial revenue in the first three months of this year.

In the face of sharp fiscal retrenchment, spending has increased dramatically. As of March 12, Wuhan has allocated 7.116 billion yuan in financial resources for epidemic prevention and control, all of which will be used for centralized hospital construction, medical treatment, centralized quarantine and other epidemic prevention and control work, according to the China Business News, among them, 88 hospitals were supported to expand the capacity of the hospitals and admit patients. In addition, the new fire mountain and Thunder Mountain hospitals have been transformed into 33 shelter hospitals, providing 35,673 shelter hospital beds, establishing 775 centralized isolation points, and providing 51,925 centralized isolation point beds, accommodation for 315 medical teams and 35,591 medical team members.

The outbreak has brought much of Wuhan's economic activity to a standstill, severely affecting offline consumption as residents are quarantined at home. According to some current reports, the first to fall is the catering, hotel, tourism, entertainment and transportation industries, which rely heavily on cash flow and have no revenue channels to close their stores during the otherwise prosperous Spring Festival, but also need to bear the cost of rent, wages and other staff, cash flow is facing a huge test.

Luo Zhi, director of the Wuhan University, learned in a survey that a famous foot bath chain store in Wuhan was facing bankruptcy, "The rent for all the stores is 10 million yuan a month, the salary of the employees is more than 50 million yuan, and the business has lost more than 100 million yuan after more than two months. The boss is disheartened and has decided to close the store. "

This is roughly the same as the national situation. During the 2019 Spring Festival golden week, retail and catering enterprises across the country achieved sales of more than 1 trillion yuan, while 2020's Spring Festival consumption dropped significantly and the revenues of the enterprises concerned fell precipitously. According to pricewaterhousecoopers forecast, the first quarter of this year, the overall national consumer goods retail sales growth may slow by 5 to 6 percent.

"For such enterprises, if they can survive, they may be able to find the market and recover gradually. For the manufacturing sector, the consequences of long-term no-work are long-term, " Luo told China News Weekly, most manufacturing orders are signed once a year. As provinces outside Hubei resume work one after another, the market share of manufacturing enterprises in the Han Dynasty may be carved up. By the time they resume work, there may be few orders left for this year, "More importantly, if orders don't come in this year, by next year, the previous relationship may have been replaced. "

Thus, a series of conduction effect on the industrial chain —— A certain enterprise's bankruptcy on the chain may affect other enterprises in the chain.

According to the Wuhan University, 70 percent of Hubei's industrial chain is in the province, which could easily lead to widespread bankruptcies. Some big companies will survive, but they will be decimated and sales will likely fall, hurting the thousands of small and medium-sized suppliers behind them.

In e enterprises, 80% of the talent in the province, in this situation, in addition to the outflow of talent and capital, the greater consequence may be unemployment caused by the decline in consumption. Luo predicts that the disposable income of residents in Hubei Province, especially in Wuhan, will fall by at least 20 percent this year, and that falling incomes will cause a drop in consumption. A drop in consumption would also be magnified by a multiplier effect, as a lack of consumption would further trigger a shortfall in demand and supply, leading to more bankruptcies.

As a result, Luo and her team produced three research reports in just a few days, which were submitted in early March to the policy research departments of the Hubei Provincial Government and the Wuhan provincial government, hoping to attract the attention of relevant departments. "Wuhan must shift its focus from fighting the epidemic to the economy and put the resumption of production back on the agenda, or it will be too late. "

In fact, authorities in Hubei Province and Wuhan have already begun to study countermeasures. It is reported that in early March, the Government of the People's Republic of China of Hubei Province has organized the Wuhan University, Huazhong University of Science and Technology and other relevant economists to analyze the current economic situation.

The above-mentioned person from Wuhan's Development and Reform Commission, who did not wish to be named, also told China News weekly that on March 6, Wuhan Mayor Zhou Xianwang had held a special meeting to study the issue of enterprises returning to work and production. Before that, wuhan Development and Reform Commission and other macro-management departments have carried out a pilot study, some statistical data are being revised discussions.

According to statistics released by the Wuhan government last year, Wuhan achieved a regional gross domestic product of 335.748 billion yuan in the first quarter of 2019, up 8.4 percent from the same period a year earlier, the highest in 13 quarters since the first quarter of 2016, than the national average.

But affected by the epidemic, Wuhan in January and February this year, relevant economic data has not yet been released.

Differential rework

The epidemic situation in Wuhan is moving in a positive direction. On March 6, the number of newly diagnosed cases in Wuhan dropped to double digits, and on March 11, the number of newly diagnosed cases dropped to single digits.

At the same time, preparations for the resumption of work are also quietly underway. At the end of February, Hubei Multi-land Online "Hubei Health Code" Application System, health code is divided into "red, yellow, green" three colors, combining the self-declaration of individuals and the automatic examination and verification of Epidemic Prevention Information by government departments, the two-dimensional code is automatically generated as an electronic pass during epidemic prevention, and Health Code is presented and inspected at various checkpoints, and only those who have a green code can pass, holding "Yellow Code" and "Red Code" requires isolation and medical treatment.

On March 9, a day before the scheduled resumption of work, Ying Yong, the party secretary of Hubei Province and commander of the provincial command for the prevention and control of the new pneumonia, called a meeting and called for the implementation of regional and hierarchical control according to the level of risk of the epidemic, on the basis of implementing the management of "Health Code" of personnel in the province, the safe and orderly flow of personnel and the classification of enterprises should be promoted timely.

Later that night, two red-headed documents circulated on the Internet, namely, the approval from the Wuhan Development Zone (Hannan) headquarters for the prevention and control of the new crown pneumonia, agreeing that the Dongfeng Honda and the suppliers would resume work, and the new Jiangxia District crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters approved approval of SAIC General Wuhan Branch 38 supporting enterprises outside the personnel orderly return to Han, signed the date is March 9.

The next morning, "China News weekly" to the Wuhan Development Zone to verify, said the other side did not know, also need to verify, but as of press time, still no response.

At the time, the situation in Wuhan was not clear until the evening of March 10, when Xi Jinping, president of the General Secretary of the Communist Party of China and President of the Central Military Commission, visited Wuhan to review the prevention and control of the epidemic, and asked that under the premise of strengthening prevention and control, take the strategy of differentiation, timely start-up zoning classification, classification classification, conditional resumption of production. This speech conveys the attitude and confidence of the central government.

On the morning of March 11, Qianjiang, Hubei Province, issued notice 26, announcing the lifting of the closure, but soon announced the cancellation of notice 26, to continue to implement strict traffic control, personnel control. The move has further complicated the situation in Hubei Province.

At 2:00 p.m. that day, the website of the Government of the People's Republic of China issued a notice to classify low, medium and high risk areas in the province, taking the county as the unit, and to implement differentiated prevention and control by division. When enterprises are classified and classified, they will be able to resume production under certain conditions, flexible and dynamic management is carried out in specific industries. Among them, Wuhan is involved in ensuring that the necessary prevention and control of the epidemic, the operation of Public Utilities, the People's Daily needs, agricultural production needs, and other enterprises involved in the important national economy and people's livelihood can resume production.

In addition, the circular states that enterprises that have a major impact on the national and global industrial chains can resume production after approval according to procedures, on the premise that prevention and control measures are in place and the responsibility for prevention and control is fulfilled, enterprises that have not suspended work or business operations since the Spring Festival may continue production.

According to the Wuhan City Development and Reform Commission official, who spoke on the condition of anonymity, Wuhan has set up a headquarters for enterprises to resume work and production, based in the city's economic and Trade Commission.

However, Wuhan's economic and Credit Commission denied the claim to China Newsweek, saying that the main lead unit is the municipal development and Reform Commission, which is only responsible for the study and formulation of policies for industrial enterprises to return to work and production. As to which enterprises are involved in the important national economy and people's livelihood and have a significant impact on the national and global industrial chain, the Wuhan Economic and Credit Commission did not give further explanation.

Comprehensive Information from all sides, whether the enterprise reply, which enterprises will be approved, the decision-making power in the hands of the new crown pneumonia epidemic prevention and control headquarters. In the literal sense, most of the service industry, which relies heavily on cash flow, and the small and medium-sized enterprises that have no voice in the industrial chain, are not in the ranks of this resumption of work. The resumption date has been postponed again, and the resumption of work is scheduled to resume no earlier than March 20 at 2400 hours.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Employees of Wuhan Xinxin Integrated Circuit Manufacturing Co. , Ltd. Inspect chip manufacturing equipment on Feb. 14. During the outbreak, the company continued to produce. Photo / Xinhua

For restarted enterprises, employees can use the health code "Green Code" , and the inflow in Hubei Province to take "point-to-point" transport flow, in other words, employees can only take the designated means of transport to and from work, urban public transport will continue to be suspended.

A director of a communications company who has resumed work told China News weekly that in order to ensure safety and control during the resumption of work, the company needs to send buses to pick up employees one by one and provide dormitories for employees, ensure each person a single room, employees can not be free to go out after returning to work, food and accommodation must be in the company and dormitory, in addition, there are two daily temperature report.

The headquarters of this enterprise is not in Hubei, and other branches have resumed work one after another. The head office did not request the Wuhan Branch to resume work. According to the head of this branch, it was relatively safe to resume work at the end of March, did Not expect the next customer to apply for resumption of work, will they as a supplier together application, after approval had to resume work ahead of schedule.

"It took about five days for the application to be approved, " said the person in charge. First, the company needs to submit an application to the district new cap epidemic prevention and control headquarters, display the stocks of epidemic prevention materials, and arrange special personnel to monitor the staff, to ensure the epidemic prevention safety during the resumption of work.

However, the staff's desire to return to work is not strong, a mobilization, only 20% of the staff, "can only meet the core product delivery. ". After resuming work, the cost is sure to increase, but the above-mentioned person in charge said that as long as can resume work, can deliver the product, will certainly have the profit, "only than usual profit may be reduced by half" .

The person in charge is more worried about the flow -- how does the raw material get in and the product get out? He has applied for a major customer channel for SF Express, but the situation is not ideal. According to his calculations, the current material can only sustain production for two weeks, if two weeks after the material still can not come in, workers will face the awkward situation of no work.

From the national situation, the resumption of work and production is not ideal. China Construction Third Bureau has analyzed the resumed projects in other areas, and found that it is expected to take more than 15 days from the preparation of the resumed resources to the full resumption of production, and in some places there is a 14-day isolation requirement for field staff. "As Wuhan is likely to be the last place to resume work and production, logistics and resource supplies in other cities should be opened up before then. It is expected that the time between the resumption of work and the resumption of normal production in Wuhan will be shortened to about seven days. "

The harsh requirements for the resumption of work, the resumption date will be extended again. As of March 13, a Dongfeng Motor Group technician told China Newsweek that the company had not yet received a notice to resume work. "Wuhan is so big, so the premise of resuming work should be to resume public transportation. Should we walk to work? "

"fighting the epidemic is the biggest politics of all. "

In any case, the return to work and production of graded subdivisions and time-division has been a big step in economic recovery, but whether this step can be effectively implemented remains to be seen.

One issue of concern is that many civil servants from government agencies at all levels, from Hubei Province to Wuhan, are sinking into communities to fight the epidemic.

China Newsweek asked a number of public officials in the Han Dynasty to find out whether it was the provincial level, the city level and the district level, the business department or the administrative department that had a hard demand on the community of civil servants sinking. The staff of the provincial organs requested to subside nearby, while the staff of the organs below the municipal government not only requested to subside, but also supervised by the supervisory group. In addition, city-owned companies such as Hankou Bank require that most employees sink into the community while securing some outlets.

At that time, Wuhan organized more than 50,000 Party members and cadres at all levels of Party and government organs, enterprises and institutions, more than 30,000 community cadres and more than 50,000 volunteers to sink into communities, according to official statistics released on February 28 in Wuhan, "We will carry out a step-by-step investigation in the form of a dragnet, leaving no dead spots or blank spaces so that we can collect all the information we need. "

"In the early stages of the fight against the epidemic, the community with government workers can play a certain role, but at this stage, the government should take a more scientific, rational and effective approach to prevent and control the epidemic, instead of making the fight against the epidemic the main task all the time, regardless of stages, regions and circumstances, " Zhang Yansheng, a principal researcher at the China Center for International Economic Exchanges, told China News Weekly.

In Zhang Yansheng's view, at present, the number of newly diagnosed cases in Wuhan is becoming smaller and smaller every day. The areas outside Wuhan are mainly the control of imported cases, with the focus on the control and prevention of the epidemic situation after resuming work, returning to production and classes, and normalizing economic and social life, community epidemic prevention work can be handed over to big data and professionals, to the transparency of information and the consciousness of citizens, to the coordination mechanism of the competent authorities in the places of export and import, thus freeing the functional organs of the government from the anti-epidemic work, the focus of our work is to return to the normal economic, cultural and social life, with the smooth flow of logistics, capital, information and talents.

"But the problem now is that fighting the epidemic is the biggest political issue. We don't organize to return to work, and we don't take responsibility. But if there is a new epidemic after the resumption of work, the people in charge will bear a lot of responsibility, which also limits the enthusiasm of all places to return to work, " Zhang said, it is imperative that those in charge should seek a balance between the scientific fight against epidemic diseases and the orderly resumption of work.

Previously, the judgment of various parties on the economic restart of Wuhan was to first lift the seal, then resume work and production. However, judging from the recent series of operations in Hubei Province, due to the heavy resistance to lift the seal, coupled with the fact that most newly diagnosed cases in the country are currently imported from abroad, it may be more appropriate to divide the area into different levels of management and control in the province, then resume work and production according to the classification time, wake up the economic activity and then release the seal according to the epidemic situation.

Luo Zhi believes that the resumption of work can follow the principle of priority, there are employee dormitories and dining halls of enterprises, high degree of automation, large capital-intensive enterprises and foreign trade enterprises can first resume work. As for the remaining enterprises, the government should issue a unified standard of epidemic prevention procedures, through the process to check the enterprises, to meet the standards can resume work. Even if some small and medium-sized enterprises can not reach the canteen and dormitory conditions, can be rented through the hotel, food and beverage distribution to achieve, "way than difficult! "

"For Wuhan, what is most needed now is to resume work in the short term and central government policy in the long term, " Luo said.

Save yourself and save others

Recently, the economic and Credit Commission of Wuhan has published two editions of the compendium of policies on benefiting enterprises in responding to the epidemic in Wuhan, which contains 132 policies at all levels from the central government to the provinces, municipalities and municipalities, as well as detailed rules for their implementation. However, Luo Zhi found in his research that, the impact of these policies on the ground is not obvious. Private entrepreneurs told her that while the government has many tax breaks and social security exemptions, they are ex post policies for businesses that can not quench their thirst and can not survive without cash flow.

In the view of Central University of Finance and Economics professor Wen Laicheng, since the national two sessions have not yet been held, in order to cope with the tight financial situation in Wuhan, it is possible to make appropriate adjustments to the budget and increase the special transfer payments to Hubei and Wuhan, increase the debt limit of Hubei Province. Some special funds and projects scattered in various ministries and departments can also be linked up with Hubei and Wuhan. In addition, the mode of post-disaster reconstruction in Wenchuan County can also be used to support the economic development of cities in Hubei Province.

Wuhan itself, by its own power, is in a well-connected region and could adopt more flexible policies, such as modest increases in the supply of land or tax breaks for badly damaged industries, help the enterprise to have the rapid growth afterward, will the loss reduce to the minimum. In addition, the deficit rate could be moderately relaxed and growth could be driven by investment.

This year, Wuhan has proposed 230 major projects at the municipal level, with private investment accounting for more than 52 per cent of the total. And this round of investment, from the current situation announced by a number of provinces across the country, not the traditional railway foundation, but mainly new infrastructure. Zhang Yansheng believes that Wuhan has the conditions to invest in new infrastructure. Wuhan has a light valley, a Yangtze River memory chip, a Wuhan Jingkai district, a Yangtze River new city, and a East L. Laboratory, "In the future, the focus of new infrastructure construction will be on new technologies represented by the new generation of information technologies such as 5g, which is an upgraded version of traditional infrastructure such as transportation, energy and new energy, and information and communication, as well as an improved version of social infrastructure. By taking advantage of these advantages, a new Wuhan will be built after the epidemic. ".

In recent years, Wuhan has made great efforts to develop the New Economy, increasing R & D Investment and promoting the development of new driving forces. According to this year's Wuhan Municipal Government Work Report, in 2019, the total R & D expenditure of the whole society increased by 10% over last year. Zhang Yansheng once classified the research and development intensity of Hubei Province (mainly Wuhan) as the second echelon of the country, which was investment-driven. In the Wuhan two sessions before the outbreak of the epidemic, the Wuhan Government Work REPORT PLANS TO INCREASE R & D spending by 10 percent this year.

However, with the outbreak of the epidemic, the sharp drop in fiscal revenue and the huge expenditure incurred in preparing for the military games last year, it is still difficult for Wuhan to achieve the "three guarantees" (guaranteeing wages, guaranteeing operation and protecting people's livelihood) in fiscal expenditure this year, spending more on research and development is harder to imagine.

From the external power point of view, Wuhan is difficult to rely on its own economic recovery, on the one hand by private investment, on the other hand by the central policy support.

From the perspective of private investment, how to make rational use of Wuhan's huge alumni and Chu business resources, testing the wisdom of the government. On February 22, Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission Secretary General Chen Yixin, soon after returning to Wuhan as the deputy head of the Central Guidance Group, met with alumni and Chu merchants to encourage them to continue giving back to society and work together to win the Battle of Wuhan. Subsequently, Alumni Chu business launched the "White Angel Employment Guarantee Program" , with more than 20,000 jobs dedicated to the children of first-line hospital staff.

On March 12, Chen Yixin met again with Chu Entrepreneurs at Zhuoer Bookstore in Wuhan and asked them to win the "second battle" . Gathered around the table were Huang Li, chairman of Wuhan Gaode Infrared Company; Yan Zhi, Chairman of Zhuoer Holdings; Zeng Wentao, CEO of Zhongjia Capital; and Jian Hongyuan, Secretary General of the Chu Merchants Association. Chen Dongsheng, chairman of Taikang Insurance Group; Lei Jun, Chairman of Xiaomi Technology; Sun Hongbin, Chairman of SUNAC; and Mao Zhenhua, chairman of Zhongcheng Group, also participated in the discussion via video link. In the future, Chu Merchants and alumni resources may play a greater role in the "defense battle" of Wuhan's economic recovery.

In addition to enterprise resources, how to win support from the central government for more national major scientific installations, major scientific projects and major scientific research projects is also the key to the future development of Wuhan. In Zhang's view, the outbreak, while revealing the shortcomings of social and public governance in Wuhan, may also present some significant opportunities for the city. Starting with the public health governance system, if the central government can give Wuhan more opportunities to advance the reform and opening up in the new era in the future, starting with the public health and modernization of public governance systems and capabilities demonstration areas, wuhan will be able to achieve greater development.
